-- Spain's Abertis Plans to Sell Brisa, Atlantia Stakes, Confidencial Reports
-- Paul Tobin
-- 2010-07-15T06:34:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/spain-s-abertis-plans-to-sell-brisa-atlantia-stakes-confidencial-reports.html

          
          
             Abertis Infraestructuras SA will 
sell its 14.5 percent stake in Brisa-Auto Estradas de Portugal 
SA and its 6 percent stake in Atlantia SpA ahead of a planned 
takeover bid led by CVC Capital Partners Ltd., El Confidencial 
reported, citing unidentified people at the companies.  
 Abertis aims to raise about 450 million euros by selling 
its Brisa stake through a convertible bond sale, while it plans
to raise about 550 million euros by selling its Atlantia stake 
in the market, the financial news website said. Abertis will 
pay a special dividend with the amounts raised, El Confidencial
said.   
